1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 18 O.S. 2021, Section 1001, is
3 amended to read as follows:
4 Section 1001.
5 SHORT TITLE
6 Sections 1001 through 1144 1144-1 of this title and Sections 18
7 and 25 through 27 of this act shall be known and may be cited as the
8 “Oklahoma General Corporation Act”. Section captions are part of
9 the Oklahoma General Corporation Act.
10 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 18 O.S. 2021, Section 1016, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 Section 1016.
13 SPECIFIC POWERS
14 Every corporation created pursuant to the provisions of the
15 Oklahoma General Corporation Act shall have power, whether or not
16 such power is provided for in the certificate of incorporation, to:
17 1. Have perpetual succession by its corporate name, unless a
18 limited period of duration is stated in its certificate of
19 incorporation;
20 2. Sue and be sued in all courts and participate, as a party or
21 otherwise, in any judicial, administrative, arbitrative or other
22 proceeding, in its corporate name;
23
24
