4 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1027.1 of Title 18, unless there
6 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 SUBMISSION OF MATTERS TO SHAREHOLDER VOTE
8 A corporation may agree to submit a matter to a vote of its
9 shareholders whether or not the board of directors determines at any
10 time after approving such matter that such matter is no longer
11 advisable and recommends that the shareholders reject or vote
12 against the matter.
13 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1027.2 of Title 18, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 AUTHORIZATION OF AGREEMENTS AND OTHER INSTRUMENTS
17 A. If any section in the Oklahoma General Corporation Act
18 expressly requires the board of directors to approve or take other
19 action with respect to any agreement, instrument, or document, such
20 agreement, instrument, or document may be approved by the board of
21 directors in final form or in substantially final form.
22 B. If the board of directors acted to approve or take other
23 action with respect to an agreement, instrument, or document that is
24 required by the Oklahoma General Corporation Act to be filed with
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3498 SFLR Page 10
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 the Secretary of State or referenced in any certificate so filed,
2 the board of directors may, at any time after providing such
3 approval or taking such other action and before the effectiveness of
4 such filing with the Secretary of State, adopt a resolution
5 ratifying the agreement, instrument, or document. A ratification
6 under this subsection shall be deemed to be effective as of the time
7 of the original approval or other action by the board of directors
8 and to satisfy any requirement under the Oklahoma General
9 Corporation Act that the board of directors approve or take other
10 action with respect to such agreement, instrument or document in a
11 specific manner or sequence. Ratification under this subsection
12 shall not be deemed to be the exclusive means of ratifying an
13 agreement, instrument, or document approved by the board of
14 directors under this section but shall be in addition to any
15 ratification or validation that may be available under Sections
16 1055.1 or 1055.2 of Title 18 of the Oklahoma Statutes or under
17 common law.
